comment: [Observable in enhanced video] Antetokounmpo (MIL) moves his pivot foot.
[Detectable with stop watch] Monroe (MIL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Brogdon (MIL) makes contact with Thomas (BOS) that affects his SQBR.
Bradley (BOS) makes incidental contact with Brogdon (MIL) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] PXP shows that Crowder (BOS) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Crowder (BOS) makes body to body contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL) that affects his shot attempt.
[Detectable with stop watch] PXP shows that Antetokounmpo (MIL) takes longer than the allowed 10 seconds to attempt his free throw.
Snell (MIL) dislodges Crowder (BOS), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
[Observable in enhanced video] LATR shows Antetokounmpo (MIL) step inside the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Monroe (MIL) sets the screen on Bradley (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LO SLA shows that Horford (BOS) is not in a legal guarding position and makes foot to foot contact with Brogdon (MIL) that affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] LATR shows Thomas (BOS) change his pivot foot.
Smart (BOS) makes incidental contact with Middleton (MIL) off ball.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is in the lane but the shot is imminent when the count reaches three.
Bradley (BOS) makes incidental contact with Brogdon (MIL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Thomas (BOS) exits the lane within three seconds.
Horford (BOS) makes contact with the ball and any contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) hand is considered incidental.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Horford (BOS) sets the screen on Brogdon (MIL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Thomas (BOS) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact with Middleton (MIL) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Monroe (MIL) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Bradley (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Brogdon (MIL) that does not affect his SQBR and jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Brogdon (MIL) released his shot attempt prior to the expiration of the shot clock is confirmed.
Middleton (MIL) legally contests the shot attempt by Smart (BOS). Any contact to the body is initiated by Smart and considered incidental.
